            <h2>About the White Rhinoceros</h2>
            <p>The white rhinoceros, also known as the square-lipped rhinoceros, is the largest extant species of rhinoceros. It is one of the five species of rhinoceros that still exist and is native to South Africa.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="why">
            <h2>Why Save Them</h2>
            <p>White rhinoceroses are under threat due to poaching for their horns and habitat loss. It is crucial to protect these magnificent creatures to maintain biodiversity and ecological balance.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="help">
            <h2>How You Can Help</h2>
            <p>There are several ways you can contribute to saving the white rhinoceros:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Donate to wildlife conservation organizations.</li>
                <li>Raise awareness about the plight of the white rhinoceros.</li>
                <li>Support sustainable practices and oppose poaching.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

